sanders
['sα:ndəz, 'san-]
(also sanderswood)
■ noun the timber of the red sandalwood, from which a red dye is obtained.
Origin
ME: from OFr. sandre, var. of sandle 'sandalwood'.

sentences.en: But White House spokeswoman Sarah Sanders said Trump was merely being polite. “It’s a common courtesy. When a military official from another government salutes… you return that,” Sanders said.
